            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.20672/figures/workflow/workflow2.jpeg",
                "caption": "Figure 2:End-to-end parametric workflow.A short prompt is expanded by a VLM into a structured JSON that includes numeric bounding boxes and RGB values (for clarity, we show only the parametric fields for the woman).\nThe JSON is then provided to BBQ to generate an image. Users can edit specific fields (e.g., box coordinates or color values), and BBQ updates the output accordingly while preserving unrelated content, demonstrating native disentanglement.\nNotably, BBQ receives no image input, and consistency is maintained solely through the disentangle structured conditioning.",
                "position": 101
            }
        ]
    },
